cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper involves the use of automatic speech recognition (ASR) and neural networks (NN) for language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of deep neural networks (DNNs) for acoustic modeling suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The adaptation of the DNNs for in-domain acoustic modeling may also relate to signal processing (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SD).
